  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nI increased heap memory to 3GB and was able to reach the finalized state after long infinality period, however it crashed due to ArchiveBlocks task:\r\n```\r\n2020-11-08 04:21:52 [CHORES]           info: @@@ archiveBlocks number of canonical blocks 77614\r\n2020-11-08 04:21:52 [CHORES]           info: @@@ archiveBlocks getting canonical blocks from db\r\n2020-11-08 04:21:52 [CHAIN]            info: Checkpoint justified epoch=20559, root=0x135a6b7134b11ff838848dfe37a2daafccaeda333de83cd50981d4635dc59b98\r\n2020-11-08 04:21:52 [CHAIN]            info: Checkpoint finalized epoch=20557, root=0x3fabb30bf04bc51c87a232ba81919821547c5f822f3305665df127577a234f87\r\n```\r\nWe should be able to separate the job into smaller batches/chunks instead of loading 77614 blocks from db and process all of them at the same time.\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nWe run ArchiveBlocks task successfully\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n```\r\nnode --max-old-space-size=3072 --inspect  lib/index.js beacon --testnet medalla --root-dir .medalla.weak\r\n```\r\n",
